Heat oven to 450 degrees F. Place crust on cookie sheet. Mix peanut butter, peanut satay sauce, sesame oil and red pepper flakes in small bowl until blended. Combine 1/4 cup peanut mixture with chicken in a medium bowl. Spread remaining peanut mixture over pizza crust. Top with chicken mixture and 1 1/2 cups cheese. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and golden. Remove pizza from oven. Top with shredded carrots, green onion, cilantro and remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Cut and serve.